         <abstract>
            <p>Lehmer's method for finding a zero of a polynomial is a procedure for searching the complex plane in such a way that a zero is isolated in a sequence of disks of decreasing radii. In this paper modifications of the method that improve its stability are given. The convergence of the method and the use of the resulting approximate zero to deflate the polynomial are discussed.</p>
         </abstract>
